    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "We have a very generic [SignatureBouncer](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/blob/v1.9.0/contracts/access/SignatureBouncer.sol) that will revert if the call doesn't comes signed from one of the approved bouncers.\r\n\r\nI think that if we make the bouncer a contract that verifies an EC signature, and then forwards the call adding their signature, this solves the example that Manu is giving. And many other things can be build on top of that. @shrugs can you please confirm if we can close this issue or if there's something missing?",
